    ],
    comment: '<p>The <code>small-caps</code> keyword forces the use of small capital letters for lower case characters. Some fonts might not support this.</p>\n<pre><code class="language-css">p.smallcaps {\n  font-variant: small-caps;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>For example, if the property is applied on the following html code:</p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x3C;p class="smallcaps"> Hello World &#x3C;/p>\n</code></pre>\n<p>All letters will be displayed in upper-case and the original lower-case letters will remain the same size as they would have been in lower-case.</p>\n<p><?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><svg width="100%" height="auto" viewBox="0 0 612 200" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.2" baseProfile="tiny"><desc>Created by HiQPdf</desc><defs></defs><rect x="0" y="0" width="612" height="200" fill="#596193"/><text x="30" y="60" style="font-size:35px;fill: #fff; font-family:&#x27;Roboto&#x27;, sans-serif;">This is a normal font-variant.</text><text x="30" y="160" style="font-size:35px;fill: #fff; font-family:&#x27;Roboto&#x27;, sans-serif;font-variant:small-caps;">This is font-variant: small-caps.</text></svg></p>\n',
